<p>Choose the preferred Network class, which is determined by its first bit=
s, by clicking either three options:</p>
<ul>
<li plerdy-tracking-id=3D"87612415501">Select the target Prefix Length in t=
he dropbox. Choose from the range of /1 to /128</li>
<li plerdy-tracking-id=3D"43475835501">Enter the IP address. An example IPv=
6 address is ready to use</li>
</ul>
<p>Hit the Calculate button to view the result list of all the network and =
IP address values.</p>
<p>Enter the IP address. An example IPv6 address is ready to use.</p>
<ul>
<li plerdy-tracking-id=3D"86813539301"><strong>Prefix Length:</strong>IPv6 =
prefix-length is the same as the IPv4 subnet mask. It is in four octets wri=
tten as an integer between 1 through 128</li>
<li plerdy-tracking-id=3D"79324452201"><strong>IP Address:</strong>IPv6 is =
written in hexadecimal format, with colons (:) between 8 groups of 16 bits,=
 for a total of (8 x 16 =3D 128) bits. The IPv6 address is represented as x=
:x:x:x:x:x:x:x, ranges from 0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000 to ffff=
:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff</li>
</ul></div>
